str2: Answer, bid, bring word, command. A primary verb; to speak or say.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
From paraballo; a similitude, i.e. fictitious narrative, apothegm or adage.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Feminine of a derivative of the base of chasma through the idea of empty expanse; room, i.e. A space of territory.

str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.
Rich, abounding in, wealthy; subst: a rich man. From ploutos; wealthy; figuratively, abounding with.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.

str2: To bear well, bring a good harvest, yield abundantly. From eu and phoreo; to bear well, i.e. Be fertile.
